                        <msContents>
                            <textLang mainLang="la"/>
                            <msItem defective="true">
                                <locus from="1r" to="3v" scheme="folios"/>
                                <title type="desc">Calendar (fragmented)</title>
                                <note>
                                    <p> The three first leaves of the calendar are missing, leaving only the months of July-December. Notable feasts:</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="1r" to="1r" scheme="folios"/>: St Alexius (17 July);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="1r" to="1r" scheme="folios"/>: St Birgitta (23 July, the date of her death, here recorded as the <quote>translatio</quote>);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="1r" to="1r" scheme="folios"/>: St Anne (26 July);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="1r" to="1r" scheme="folios"/>: St Botvid (28 July);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="1r" to="1r" scheme="folios"/>: St Olof (29 July);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="1r" to="1r" scheme="folios"/>: St Elin (31 July);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="1v" to="1v" scheme="folios"/>: Transfiguration of Jesus (6 Aug.);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="2r" to="2r" scheme="folios"/>: St Marcellus (4 Sep.);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="2r" to="2r" scheme="folios"/>: Sts Gorgonius and Dorotheus (9 Sep.);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="2r" to="2r" scheme="folios"/>: Wenceslaus (28 Sep.);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="2v" to="2v" scheme="folios"/>: Translation of St Eskil (6 Oct.);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="2v" to="2v" scheme="folios"/>: St Birgitta (7 Oct. with the octave 14 Oct.);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="2v" to="2v" scheme="folios"/>: St Cordula (22 Oct.);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="3v" to="3v" scheme="folios"/>: St Anne (9 Dec.).</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="2r" to="2r" scheme="folios"/>: An obit entry on 12 September was added 1575, see Additions.</p>
                                    <p/>
                                    <p/>
                                </note>
                                <bibl>
                                    <title type="short" ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/bibl/107249">Kroon (1951)</title>
                                    <citedRange from="27" to="32" unit="page"/>
                                </bibl>
                            </msItem>
                        </msContents>
                        <physDesc>
                            <objectDesc>
                                <supportDesc material="paper">
                                    <support>
                                        <p>
                                            <locus from="1r" to="3v" scheme="folios"/>
                                            <material>Western paper</material>
                                            <dimensions type="leaf">
                                                <height quantity="285" unit="mm"/>
                                                <width quantity="205" unit="mm"/>
                                            </dimensions>
                                            <watermark n="1">
                                                <locusGrp>
                                                    <locus from="1r" to="1r" scheme="folios"/>
                                                </locusGrp>
                                                <term type="watermarkMotif">Bull's head with eyes and nostrils, single-line rod and star above, similar to Piccard II:2, VII, 385.</term>
                                            </watermark>
                                        </p>
                                    </support>
                                    <extent>
                                        <measure type="textblockLeaves" quantity="3" unit="folios"/>
                                    </extent>
                                    <condition>The three extant leaves are what remains of an original ternion. The paper is brittle. Outer cornes are lost and edges are fraying. Burn marks on outer margin on <locus from="1r" to="1r" scheme="folios"/> are showing through to the rest of the leaves in the quire.</condition>
                                </supportDesc>
                                <layoutDesc>
                                    <layout columns="1">
                                        <locus from="1r" to="3v" scheme="folios"/>
                                        <dimensions type="written">
                                            <height quantity="220" unit="mm"/>
                                            <width unit="mm" max="140" min="135"/>
                                        </dimensions>
                                        <note>Columns for the calendar are ruled in brown-black ink.</note>
                                    </layout>
                                </layoutDesc>
                            </objectDesc>
                            <handDesc>
                                <handNote sameAs="hand-1">
                                    <locus from="1r" to="3v" scheme="folios"/>
                                </handNote>
                            </handDesc>
                            <additions>
                                <p>
                                    <locus from="1r" to="3v" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <note>The names of the months and number of days have been added by a different hand.</note>
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                    <locus from="2r" to="2r" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <note>For 12 September in the calendar: <quote xml:lang="la">In Christe ex hac lacrimarum vallis emigressa est Filia mea Anna, quae in hac templo sepulta est hoc ipso die Anno domini 1575 Matthias Olaui Dingtunensis</quote>.</note>
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                    <locus from="2v" to="2v" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <note>In the outer margin in black ink by a 16th-century hand is added a text in Swedish, partly lost due to wear of the paper, see <bibl>
                                            <title type="short" ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/bibl/107249">Kroon (1951)</title>
                                            <citedRange from="30" to="30" unit="page"/>
                                            <citedRange from="1" to="1" unit="footnote"/>
                                        </bibl>.</note>
                                </p>
                            </additions>
                            <decoDesc>
