                        <msContents>
                            <textLang mainLang="la"/>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="4ra" to="4rb" scheme="folios"/>
                                <textLang mainLang="la"/>
                                <title type="desc">Blessing and sprinkling of holy water</title>
                                <rubric>Sacerdos in dominicis diebus celebraturus in alba et stola paratus priusquam planetam seu casulam induat <gap reason="editorial"/> Sequitur exorzismus salis tonaliter dicendo Adiutorium Deinde conspergitur aqua cum Antiphona</rubric>
                                <incipit>Asperges me</incipit>
                                <explicit>cum omnibus sanctis in aduentu filii tui domini nostri ihesu christo celesti gloria perfrui mereamur per eundem dominum</explicit>
                                <note>The antiphon is set to two different melodies depending on the degree of solemnity. It is followed by three collects.</note>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="4rb" to="106ra" scheme="folios"/>
                                <title type="desc">Proper of time</title>
                                <rubric>Dominica prima in aduentu officium Dominica prima aduentus domini Officium</rubric>
                                <incipit>
                                    <supplied reason="omitted" xml:lang="la">A</supplied>d te leuaui (Ps. 24:1) </incipit>
                                <explicit>Quod autem dico vobis omnibus dico vigilate (Mark 13:37)</explicit>
                                <finalRubric xml:lang="la">Explicit missale de tempore ab aduentu vsque in aduentum domini finitum</finalRubric>
                                <note>
                                    <p> The proper of time begins with the First Sunday of Advent and ends with the Twenty-fourth Sunday after Trinity and the mass for the Sunday before the First Sunday of Advent. All songs are fully notated. One bifolium is lost between <locus from="89v" to="89v" scheme="folios"/> and <locus from="90r" to="90r" scheme="folios"/>, resulting in the loss of the end of the Sixth Sunday after Trinity and the beginning of the Seventh Sunday after Trinity.</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="37v" to="37Ar" scheme="folios"/>: guidelines and ruling but no text. No loss of text between <locus from="37v" to="37v" scheme="folios"/> and <locus from="38r" to="38r" scheme="folios"/>.</p>
                                </note>
                                <bibl>
                                    <title type="short" ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/bibl/107258">Johansson (1951)</title>
                                    <citedRange from="187" to="191" unit="page"/>
                                    <note>Benedictions of the palms for Palm Sunday</note>
                                </bibl>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="106ra" to="106vb" scheme="folios"/>
                                <title type="desc">Dedication of the church</title>
                                <rubric>Sequitur de dedicacione ecclesie Officium</rubric>
                                <incipit>
                                    <supplied reason="omitted">T</supplied>erribilis est locus iste </incipit>
                                <explicit>dum iugiter per vestigia tua graditur ad celestia promissa te ducente peruenire mereatur Per Quando hoc festum infra pascha <gap reason="editorial"/> siue sit dominica siue non cotidiana dicatur</explicit>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="106vb" to="110rb" scheme="folios"/>
                                <title type="desc">Ordo and Canon missae</title>
                                <rubric>Oracio ante altare cum genuflexione antequam induat vestes sacras</rubric>
                                <incipit>Sancti dei omnes qui ab inicio</incipit>
                                <explicit>ut cuncta nostra operacio et oracio a te semper incipiat et per te incepta finiatur Qui viuis et regnas deus per omnia secula seculorum amen</explicit>
                                <finalRubric>Et sic est finis laudetur deus in celis</finalRubric>
                                <note>
                                    <p> This part begins with the priest's prayers before Mass and ends with prayers to be said after Mass. The prefaces are set to music.</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="109rb" to="109rb" scheme="folios"/>: The canon. The initial has been cut out. No canon image.</p>
                                </note>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="110va" to="123vb" scheme="folios"/>
                                <title type="desc">Proper of saints (fragmented)</title>
                                <rubric>
                                    <!--Text loss due to wear.-->
                                    <gap reason="damage"/>ia de <gap reason="damage"/> deficit queretur in <supplied reason="damage" xml:lang="la">commu</supplied>ni de sanctis In vigilia sancti Andree Officium </rubric>
                                <explicit defective="true">complenda preceptis domine sacris supplices te rogamus ut intercedentibus</explicit>
                                <note>
                                    <p> The Proper of saints begins with the vigil for St Andrew (29 Nov.). An unknown number of quires are missing between <locus from="113v" to="113v" scheme="folios"/> and <locus from="114r" to="114r" scheme="folios"/>, resulting in the loss of most of the feast of the Purification (2 Feb.) and the beginning of the feast of St John the Baptist (24 June), as well as all feasts between these dates. On account of missing quires the proper ends imperfectly with the feast for Sts Simon and Jude (28 Oct.). Notable feasts:</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="116rb" to="116rb" scheme="folios"/>: St Knut (10 July);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="117ra" to="117rb" scheme="folios"/>: St Birgitta (23 July);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="117va" to="117vb" scheme="folios"/>: St Botvid (28 July);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="117vb" to="118ra" scheme="folios"/>: St Olof (29 July);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="118ra" to="118rb" scheme="folios"/>: St Elin (31 July);</p>
                                    <p>
